He said that everyone he had met had a similar rags to riches story, and that a lot of hard work had gone into the success.	(rags)
Don't start looking for new challenges if everything is working out for the best!	(working)
"If you have too many irons in the fire, you'll certainly miss out on real opportunity" he continued.	(irons)
I've seen people as busy as a bee who never really seem to do anything.	(bee)
In other words, you need to ride the gravy train.	(train)
It's absolutely essential to never spread yourself too thin.	(thin)
"First and foremost," John said "don't believe that success is ever mana from heaven.	(mana)
